Commented on #5 Multiple language of material name

Well, yea that's expected it's client side based. Kinda strange that mc does not allow you target one language like: translate("fr-FR", { translate: "block.grass_block" }) - forces text to be in French. I think they don't allow it as only 1 language can be loaded at one time so loading other language files will use more of client space, but honestly it's just a couple of few hundred kbs at most.
Commented on #5 Multiple language of material name

I would go for LocaleLib, you can use combination of it with our own message example: linkMessage: You have linked {block} to chest Block will be translated automatically and this way no strange messages will happen.
Ye we can go for LocaleLib but just afraid user will start asking why they receive this kind of message
For Example if server's language is base on Chinese, when a player link block they should receive 你已将草块连接至箱子 But if the client is on English language, they will receive 你已将Grass Block连接至Chest
From your linkMessage, if my minecraft is on Chinese language. I will receive You have linked 草块 to chest when i link a grass block to chest
You can just in yml do: linkMessage: Fancy Chinese {block} Fancy Chinese This way block will be translated and other decided by server side
